<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="55.[151,1436,151,464]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,332,357]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species is fairly similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[669,893,332,357]" class="Oligochaeta" family="Megascolecidae" genus="Metaphire" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="dorsomonotheca">
<emphasis box="[669,893,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">M. dorsomonotheca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Thai" box="[908,1174,332,357]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Thai, T. B. &amp; Samphon, K. (1988) New subspecies and species of earthworms (Oligochaeta) from Laos PDR. Journal of Science of HNUE, special issue, 3 - 25." type="book chapter" year="1988">Thai &amp; Samphon, 1988</bibRefCitation>
) from 
<collectingCountry box="[1251,1308,333,356]" name="Laos" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Laos</collectingCountry>
, but differs in having three pairs of spermathecal pores in intersegments 6/7/8/9 and larger body size. 
<bibRefCitation author="Blakemore" box="[1217,1428,367,392]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Blakemore, R. J. (2007 a) Updated checklist of Pheretimoids (Oligochaeta: Megascolecidae: Pheretima auct.) taxa. www. annelida. net / earthworm / Pheretimoids. pdf (accessed 6 Jun 2016)" type="journal article" year="2007" yearSuffix="a">Blakemore (2007a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Blakemore" box="[151,221,404,429]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Blakemore, R. J. (2008 b) List of earthworms from Cambodia, Laos, and Vietnam (Excel spreadsheet). In: A Series of Searchable Texts on Earthworm Biodiversity, Ecology and Systematics from Various Regions of the World - 2 nd Edition (2008). VermEcology, Yokohama. CD - ROM. Avaliable from: http: // www. annelida. net / earthworm / Vietnam % 20 + % 20 Lao s % 20 + % 20 Cambodia 1. xls (Accessed 21 Jul. 2016)" type="journal article" year="2008" yearSuffix="b">2008b</bibRefCitation>
) considered it as &quot; 
<emphasis box="[432,643,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">species inquirenda</emphasis>
&quot;. Material was re-examined and presence of male copulatory pouches and hence placement of the species in 
<taxonomicName box="[581,697,439,464]" class="Oligochaeta" family="Megascolecidae" genus="Metaphire" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[581,697,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Metaphire</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confirmed here.
</paragraph>
